<DOC><DOCNO> AP890418-0079 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-18-89 0956EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-France-PlanePurchase 1stLd-Writethru a05s29PercentDecreaseinQuarterlyProfit04-18 0161</FIRST><SECOND>PM-France-Plane Purchase, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0527,0162</SECOND><HEAD>Irish Company Places Biggest Plane Order in History</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: LEADS thruout to CORRECT size of new order to 308 sted 819 andlower cost of order; no pickup</HEAD><DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   GPA Group Ltd. today announced it was ordering 308planes, the largest single purchase of aircraft in aviation history.   The $16.8 billion order will be shared by the American companiesBoeing and McDonnell-Douglas, and Airbus, a European consortium,officials of the Irish aircraft-leasing company said.   A similar announcement was made in London today, and a newsconference was scheduled for New York as well.   The biggest previous aviation order _ worth $10.5 billion _ wasplaced by Delta Air Lines last September for 225 orders and optionson Boeing and McDonnell-Douglas airplanes.   The current order combines with previous orders announced in1986 to bring the total GPA buying program to 819 planes worthabout $30 billion. That figure includes some planes alreadydelivered.</TEXT></DOC>